HEADWORD: Chih hsien
<hw>Chih" hsien`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Chin. <ets>chih
hsien</ets>, lit., (He who) knows (the) district.]</ety> <def>An
official having charge of a hsien, or administrative district, in China;
a district magistrate, responsible for good order in his hsien (which
see), and having jurisdiction in its civil and criminal cases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

